</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
Program Manager starts every time you start Windows. You use Program Manager
to organize your programs, or applications, into groups.
</p><p>
Each icons in the Program Manager window represents a group.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/windows311forworkgroups/37.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
When you open a group, the applications contained in that group are displayed
in a window.
</p><p>
Open the Accessories group now by double-clicking the Accessories group
icon.
</p></td></tr>
