<p>
You can change the size of any window. You do so by changing its width
and height.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/windows311forworkgroups/66.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
You can size a window by moving the pointer slowly over the border of the
window until the pointer changes to a double-arrow pointer, and then
dragging that border until the window is the size you want.
</p><p>
Size the window now to the outline on your computer screen.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=640 height=480 src='pics/tutorials/windows311forworkgroups/67.png'></td></tr></table>
